                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4A6/365: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-30T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 30, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 30—12:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Conference today approved: (1) Turkish proposal to destroy future seizures
                    and, (2) Yugoslav proposal to destroy seized drugs in stock when convention
                    becomes operative.</p>
                <p>Although proposals were made obviously in the interest of raw material producers,
                    this delegation felt compelled to vote in favor of the principle in (1) and
                    refrained from voting on (2).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
